The People's Solidarity of Participatory Democracy, an influential civic group, filed a petition Monday with state prosecutors against Lee, Hong and the Samsung chief.
Last month, television network MBC said it had acquired a spy agency recording of a 1997 conversation between Hong Seok-hyun, then publisher of the mass-circulation JoongAng Ilbo, and Lee Hak-soo, a top executive with Samsung Group, the country's biggest industrial conglomerate.
